1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the complexity of complex networks, which is a common topic in social and information networks. 
2. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes a new method based on the Tsallis entropy to describe the complexity of complex networks, which can be applied to neural and evolutionary computing. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the structure property of complex networks, which is related to data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the relationship between nodes in complex networks, which is related to systems and control. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a new method based on entropy to describe the complexity of complex networks, which is related to information theory.
